    <briefdescription>
<para>Template class for type-specific stack nodes. </para>
    </briefdescription>
    <detaileddescription>
<para>The <ref refid="classBULKCC_1_1ObjTemplate" kindref="compound">ObjTemplate</ref> class is a concrete implementation of the <ref refid="classBULKCC_1_1Obj" kindref="compound">Obj</ref> base class that can store objects of a specific type T. It provides type-safe storage and retrieval of objects within the stack structure.</para>
<para><parameterlist kind="templateparam"><parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername>T</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>The type of object to store in this node</para>
</parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
</parameterlist>
</para>
<sect1 id="classBULKCC_1_1ObjTemplate_1overview">
<title>Overview</title>
<para>Each <ref refid="classBULKCC_1_1ObjTemplate" kindref="compound">ObjTemplate</ref> node can hold one object of type T. The object is stored as a member variable and can be added, fetched, or erased through the provided methods.</para>
</sect1>
<sect1 id="group__BULKCC_1usage">
<title>Basic Usage</title>
<para>This class is typically not used directly. Use the <ref refid="classBULKCC_1_1Controller" kindref="compound">Controller</ref> class to create and manage stacks:</para>
<para><programlisting><codeline><highlight class="normal"><ref refid="classBULKCC_1_1Controller" kindref="compound">BULKCC::Controller</ref><sp/>controller;</highlight></codeline>
<codeline><highlight class="normal">MyClass*<sp/>obj<sp/>=<sp/></highlight><highlight class="keyword">new</highlight><highlight class="normal"><sp/>MyClass();</highlight></codeline>
<codeline><highlight class="normal"><ref refid="classBULKCC_1_1Obj" kindref="compound">BULKCC::Obj</ref>*<sp/>stack<sp/>=<sp/>controller.<ref refid="classBULKCC_1_1Controller_1a20c5e4e20cc7b8f7cf5a5c8f0375327a" kindref="member">add</ref>&lt;MyClass*&gt;(obj);</highlight></codeline>
</programlisting></para>
<para><simplesect kind="see"><para><ref refid="classBULKCC_1_1Controller" kindref="compound">Controller</ref> </para>
</simplesect>
<simplesect kind="see"><para><ref refid="classBULKCC_1_1Obj" kindref="compound">Obj</ref> </para>
</simplesect>
</para>
</sect1>
    </detaileddescription>
